'''Jay North''' (born [[August 3]], [[1951]] in [[Hollywood, California]], [[United States|USA]]) is an actor best remembered for his lead role in the TV series ''[[Dennis the Menace (TV series)|Dennis the Menace]].'' Chosen for the role by creator [[Hank Ketcham]] himself,[[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0636020/bio]] North appeared in some 146 episodes of the weekly half-hour comedy.  	
 		 
He later appeared in several movies as a teen and as a young adult. He also starred in the television series ''[[Maya (TV series)|Maya]]'', with co-star [[Sajid Khan]]. He also did voice work for the [[Flintstones]]' spin-off ''[[The Pebbles and Bamm-Bamm Show]]'', where he provided the voice of a teenage [[Bamm-Bamm Rubble]]. 

Finding himself forever [[typecast]] as "Dennis the Menace," North quit acting and joined the [[United States Navy|Navy]] in the [[1970s]].[http://www.sitcomsonline.com/boards/archive/index.php/t-125059.html] He later served as a prison security guard in [[Florida]]. [http://members.tripod.com/~former_child_star/north_jay.html] He is now retired and lives in [[Lake Butler, Union County, Florida|Lake Butler, Florida]]. [http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0636020/bio]

North is the son of actor/songwriter Hal Hopper and Dorothy North. [[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0636020/bio]]
	 
